Rub the tomato halves with one tablespoon of the oil and season well with salt and freshly ground black pepper.Place on a baking tray and roast for 8-10 minutes, or until cooked and soft.Heat the remaining tablespoon of oil in a frying pan and fry the onion and garlic for 2-3 minutes, until softened.Add the bacon and fry for 2-3 minutes, or until cooked through.Add the chicken livers and fry for 2-3 minutes on both sides until golden-brown all over and completely cooked through.To serve, spoon the chicken liver mixture into the tomato halves and place onto a warm plate.